dc_title_s: Iowa County, Iowa, 1956, aerial photomosaic index
dc_description_s: Title supplied by cataloger based on information from sheet label. Image is a photoreduction of the mosaic created from original aerial photographs. Designating symbol DH. Form of individual image numbering: DH-1R-[number], DH-2R-[number], DH-3R-[number], or DH-4R-[number]."Flying completed 6-30--56" Flown by Woltz Studios, Inc. Des Moines, Iowa. "Approximate scale, 1:20,000" [refers to individual images from which mosaic was made].|Contact the Map Collection at The University of Iowa Libraries: http://www.lib.uiowa.edu/maps/contact/
